developer_understanding_on_working: The _d configuration is used in the catena function to determine the value of d, which is then used in the compTweak method to generate a tweak value. This tweak value is concatenated with the password, salt, and public input to update the hash function. The configuration affects the size of the output hash.
developer_understanding_on_triggering_fr: The _d configuration is triggered every time the catena function is called with the specified parameters.
developer_understanding_on_size_impact: The _d configuration impacts the size of the output hash generated by the catena function.
